+# Exploration 002 Goal - Class Retention, Finiteness, And Step-3 Readiness
+
+## Objective
+
+Use the Step-8 closure ledger to decide whether honest exact bookkeeping for
+`F_SS(1/12)` yields:
+
+- one finite exact closed subsystem inside the audited one-bridge class; or
+- an earlier constructive obstruction such as class exit,
+  arbitrary truncation requirement,
+  uncontrolled packet growth,
+  or exact non-isolability on the frozen ledger.
+
+This exploration must also state whether Chain Step 3 is well posed.
+
+## Success Criteria
+
+- Land one decisive Step-8 verdict with local citations:
+  finite honest closed system,
+  or a sharp closure-stage failure memo.
+- If finite closure is earned, name the exact state variables and interaction
+  table Step 3 should inherit.
+- If finite closure is not earned, name the first decisive obstruction and
+  explain why Step 3 cannot honestly begin on the current record.
+
+## Failure Criteria
+
+- It silently assumes a finite reduced ODE because the Step-4 witness looked
+  friendly on screening metrics.
+- It treats missing support-level closure data as a minor gap instead of a
+  Step-8 verdict if that gap blocks exact isolation.
+- It permits rescue by post hoc extra bridge, shell-locked mode, optional
+  companion, or alternate closure convention.
+
+## Required Local Context
+
