+# Exploration 001 Summary - Raw Exact Closure Ledger For `F_SS(1/12)`
+
+- Goal:
+  reconstruct the raw exact closure burden of the frozen witness `F_SS(1/12)`
+  on the Step-7 canonical one-bridge ledger, separating already frozen content,
+  mandatory conjugate completion, closure-forced same-scale / feedback /
+  cross-scale burden, and the point where the local record stops supporting a
+  finite exact mode list.
+- What I tried:
+  read the required Step-8, Step-7, Step-4, Step-2, Step-1, atlas-source, and
+  library files; extracted the frozen witness sheet and forced exact-NS extras;
+  compared classwise burden data against the older exact-interaction memos; and
+  searched the repo for any concrete `F_SS(1/12)` wavevector/helicity support
+  ledger or full forced-triad coefficient table.
+- Outcome:
+  succeeded for the raw closure ledger, failed to earn a finite exact
+  support-level closure list from the current repository.
+- One key takeaway:
+  the repo freezes `F_SS(1/12)` plus mandatory conjugate completion and the
+  class labels `mirror / companion / feedback / cross`, but it does not pin the
+  explicit finite support needed to turn those classwise burdens into one exact
+  closed packet ledger.
+- Leads worth pursuing:
+  write one explicit carried-witness wavevector/helicity ledger for
+  `F_SS(1/12)`; write the exact coefficient table for all desired and forced
+  triads on that ledger; fix one finite packet-closure convention and one
+  closed amplitude system before any Step-3 dynamics handoff.
+- Unexpected findings:
+  the local record is sharper than I expected at the class level: it already
+  names representative same-scale companion, mirror, long-leg feedback, and
+  cross-scale spill patterns, and it already freezes the classwise burden totals
+  at the carried witness.
+- Computations worth doing later:
+  once an explicit support ledger exists, enumerate the forced mixed-mirror and
+  shell-bridge companion modes, partition the exact closed interaction ledger
+  into `on-template` and `spectator` pieces, and derive the exact closed
+  projected amplitude system on the frozen Step-7 sheet.
