+# Exploration 002 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  decide whether honest exact bookkeeping for `F_SS(1/12)` yields one finite
+  exact closed subsystem inside the audited one-bridge class, or instead fails
+  earlier with a closure-stage obstruction; also decide whether Chain Step 3 is
+  well posed.
+- What I tried:
+  read the Step-8 goal/reasoning, the Step-7 freeze, the Step-4 dossier rules,
+  the Step-2 interaction-template report, the atlas anatomy note, the run-002
+  judgment/attack packet, `decision-011.md`, and `CHAIN.md`; then checked
+  whether any landed local file upgrades the witness from classwise forced
+  extras to one finite support closure with one exact interaction table.
+- Outcome:
+  failed to earn finite closure.
+- One key takeaway:
+  the current record freezes only the classwise forced closure burden and
+  explicitly still needs a finite packet-closure convention, so the earliest
+  decisive Step-8 verdict is exact non-isolability on the frozen ledger.
+- Leads worth pursuing:
+  only a new exact support-level closure derivation for all forced triads of
+  `F_SS(1/12)` on the same frozen ledger; nothing in the present branch record
+  justifies starting Step 3.
+- Unexpected findings:
+  the required sibling file
+  `steps/step-008/explorations/exploration-001/REPORT.md`
+  is missing, which matches the larger absence of a landed raw finite closure
+  sheet.
+- Computations worth doing later if scope changes:
+  one explicit wavevector/helicity realization and one full forced-triad
+  coefficient ledger for `F_SS(1/12)`, but only as a fresh closure derivation,
+  not as inherited Step-3 input.
+
+## Verdict
+
+- `finite honest closed system`: no.
+- `first decisive obstruction`: exact non-isolability on the frozen ledger,
+  equivalently the need for an unearned finite packet-closure convention /
+  truncation rule before any exact reduced dynamics can be posed honestly.
+- `class retention`: not earned.
+- `Chain Step 3 well posed`: no.
